Why do we need volumes in Kubernetes?

 Pods are ephemeral. If a Pod is deleted or recreated, data stored inside the Pod is lost. Volumes provide storage that applications can use to preserve or share data.

WWhich applications require persistent storage?

Examples:

MySQL
PostgreSQL
MongoDB
Elasticsearch
Jenkins
Prometheus
Grafana (for dashboards if configured to persist)
Applications that store user-uploaded files

Types of Kubernetes Volumes

├── emptyDir/simple mount
├── hostPath
