PERSISTENT VOLUME CLAIM: ( PVC )

	in simple words, it is an "REQUEST FOR THE STORAGE"

	PV = The storage = (house)
	PVC = The request to use the storage = (rental agreement)
	Pod = The application that uses the storage = (tenant)

steps:
	create the pvc.yaml file 
	kubectl apply -f pvc.yaml
	kubectl describe pvc < pod name of pvc >

in the describe section  you can see
	 status: "bounded "  when the pv size and PVC cliam size matches in both pv.yaml and pvc.yaml 
	 status: "pending " when the pvcClaim size  is more than the pv size in yaml files.


note: when the pvcclaim  size equal or less than the pv size , kuberentes will autometically binds this pvc to pv in the backend.


that is, when PV is creted inside the cluster, there is "persistenetVolume controler" which continiously watch the cluster and when it is creted it store the data in "etcd" (which is part of k8s architecture component and it will take continously backup of each and every action inside the cluster) and also when PVC is created persistenetVolume controler monitor the cluster and store the PVC data in etcd againg , 

so , when pvc is ceated, it checks the data pf PV for maching size which is mentiond in PVC and PV  , once it finds the matching size, it autometically binds both PV and PVC.

